comments.body: It’s more fern like than your suggestion. Thanks, though!

Yeah, the leaves look very fern-like on yarrow. Quite a few flowering plants have fern-like foliage. Ferns are spore-producing plants that never make flowers.

For comparison with your plant, check out the pictures of the foliage at the bottom of the page here: https://www.missouribotanicalgarden.org/PlantFinder/PlantFinderDetails.aspx?taxonid=241832
